Sheep pox and goat pox, Russia
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Jan 2021 from Dr Nikolay Vlasov, deputy head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance, Ministry of Agriculture, Moscow, Russia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Dec 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 4 Jan 2021
Report date: 16 Jan 2021
Date submitted to OIE: 16 Jan 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 16 Dec 2020
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: sheep pox and goat pox virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Batlaich, Khunzakhsky, Respublika Dagestan [Dagestan Republic]
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Dec 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases/ Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 1540 / 39 / 27 / - / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 2.53 / 1.75 / 69.23 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; screening; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; disinfection; no treatment of affected animals.
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
[Dagestan Republic; 1501 sheep vaccinated; information of the vaccine used no given]
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Stavropolskaya Veterinary Laboratory (local laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 4 Jan 2021 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

